26/08/2009
TIRANA, Albania -- Local media reported on Tuesday (August 25th) that Albania has been included in a World Health Organisation (WHO) project to combat the effects of climate change.
Albania is one of the seven Southeast European and Central Asian countries participating in the initiative.
In other news Tuesday, Kosovo police arrested an Albanian citizen, allegedly carrying illegal ammunition in his car at the border with Kosovo.
Police say 45 boxes of 6.5 calibre ammunition, each holding 70 pieces, were found in the Mercedes.
This is the third such ammunition seizure reported by Kosovo authorities this year.
(Start, Standard, Balkan Web, Panorama, Telegrafi - 25/08/09)
